## Quick Install Commands

### Option 1: Clean Install (Recommended)

```bash
# Remove node_modules and package-lock.json
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json

# Remove webpack dependencies from package.json manually
# Add vite dependencies to package.json manually

# Fresh install
npm install
```

### Option 2: Incremental Install

```bash
# Remove old dependencies
npm uninstall webpack webpack-dev-server webpack-manifest-plugin \
  html-webpack-plugin mini-css-extract-plugin css-minimizer-webpack-plugin \
  terser-webpack-plugin react-dev-utils case-sensitive-paths-webpack-plugin \
  dotenv-webpack eslint-webpack-plugin fork-ts-checker-webpack-plugin \
  react-refresh-webpack-plugin webpack-node-externals \
  duplicate-package-checker-webpack-plugin

# Install new dependencies
npm install --save-dev vite @vitejs/plugin-react vite-plugin-html \
  vite-plugin-node-polyfills vite-plugin-dts glob

# Update scripts in package.json manually
```

## Verification

After installation, verify:

```bash
# Check versions
npm list vite
npm list @vitejs/plugin-react

# Verify scripts exist
npm run start --help
npm run build:app --help

# Check for peer dependency warnings
npm ls
```

## Expected package.json Size Change

- **Before**: ~150 devDependencies
- **After**: ~140 devDependencies
- **Net change**: -10 packages (but ~370MB disk space saved)

